  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Legal Advice for Older and Disabled Prisoners</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to reform inadequate prison healthcare services, advocating for the protection of older and disabled prisoners in England and Wales. Currently, the prison system lacks sufficient staffing and resources necessary to secure prisoners&apos; right to health. By providing free legal advice and support through telephone, mail, and face-to-face outreach clinics, PAS will ensure that the medical and healthcare needs of chronically ill, disabled and older prisoners are rightfully met.</narrative>
  </description>
